TREE ADVISORY BOARD ITEMS:

OLD BUSINESS: There were no items for discussion.

NEW BUSINESS: 
- Discussion regarding Tree City USA Application and Arbor Day Activities. Below are the four standards for the Tree City USA Application:
  1. Tree board or department;
  2. Tree-care ordinance;
  3. Community forestry program with an annual budget of at least $2 per capita; and
  4. Arbor Day observance and proclamation

Items 1 and 2 were addressed under the recent adoption of Ordinance 4335 establishing Chapter 133, Fenton Tree Advisory Board, of the Municipal Code.

Item 3 is addressed under the City annual budget, which includes forestry activities including, but not limited to, tree planting, tree trimming, and tree removal.

Item 4 can be addressed by an Arbor Day proclamation by the Board of Aldermen and the Fenton Tree Advisory Board hosting an activity to promote and celebrate Arbor Day.

For discussion at the meeting, some activities the Tree Board may want to consider is hosting volunteer tree plantings in the City Parks this fall (Staff can contact Forest ReLeaf of Missouri to obtain native trees at little to no cost) or having a volunteer "park clean-up day" in one or more parks. Other ideas of activities can also be found at https://www.arborday.org/celebrate/celebration-ideas.cfm

Mary Heinemann made a motion to approve hosting a tree planting day this fall and a park clean-up day in the spring of 2024 to observe Arbor Day. (The Tree Board will select locations for the fall planting, and Staff will try and obtain trees through Forest ReLeaf of Missouri). Mike Abbott seconded the motion.

5 Ayes; 0 Nays, 2 Absent, 0 Abstain: Motion APPROVED by voice vote.

